<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFB9FFB3FDBCBF9FFD76FE4A" author="Friese, H." box="[516,670,405,431]" pageId="2" pageNumber="536" pagination="39 - 48" refId="ref6002" refString="Friese, H. (1899 a) Neue arten der Bienengattungen Epicharis Klug und Centris Fabr. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 23, 39 - 48." type="journal article" year="1899">Friese, 1899a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 46.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36D3FFB9FFB3FF7FBFB0FDA9FD4E" blockId="2.[151,1437,405,720]" pageId="2" pageNumber="536">
Type data: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFB9FFB3FEFCBFB3FE0FFE36" author="Friese, H." box="[324,487,441,467]" pageId="2" pageNumber="536" pagination="39 - 48" refId="ref6002" refString="Friese, H. (1899 a) Neue arten der Bienengattungen Epicharis Klug und Centris Fabr. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 23, 39 - 48." type="journal article" year="1899">Friese (1899a)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the type specimen was housed at 
<collectionCode id="ED42AE16FFB9FFB3FBAFBFB0FBB6FE31" box="[1047,1118,442,468]" country="Austria" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/c7yt-hh77" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="2" pageNumber="536">NMW</collectionCode>
but it is actually in 
<collectionCode id="ED42AE16FFB9FFB3FAF8BFB0FA71FE31" box="[1344,1433,442,468]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="2" pageNumber="536">HNHM</collectionCode>
. The 
<typeStatus id="54E88871FFB9FFB3FF71BFD7FEC3FE12" box="[201,299,477,503]" pageId="2" pageNumber="536">holotype</typeStatus>
male has the following data label: 
<collectingCountry id="F3447643FFB9FFB3FD08BFD7FCEEFE12" box="[688,774,477,503]" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="536">Mexico</collectingCountry>
[printed]\ [light greenish square] 36. [handwritten]\ [black- rimmed] 658 47. [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D50FFB9FFB3FDBDBC08FD79FDFE" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[517,657,513,540]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavifrons">
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFB9FFB3FDBDBC08FDF0FDF9" box="[517,536,514,540]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="536">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFB9FFB3FD9FBC0BFD79FDFE" box="[551,657,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="536">flavifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
F. 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D50FFB9FFB3FD0EBC08FC47FDFE" authority="Friese" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1899" box="[694,943,513,540]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="flavifrons" variety="flavofasciata">
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFB9FFB3FD0EBC08FD2AFDFE" box="[694,706,514,539]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="536">v</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFB9FFB3FD6ABC0BFC8BFDFE" box="[722,867,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="536">flavofasciata</emphasis>
Friese
</taxonomicName>
³ [handwritten] det. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFB9FFB3FB1EBC0BFAC3FDFE" author="Friese, H." box="[1190,1323,513,539]" pageId="2" pageNumber="536" pagination="427 - 431" refId="ref5980" refString="Friese, H. (1898) Die Trigona - Arten Australiens. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 21, 427 - 431." type="journal article" year="1898">Friese 1898</bibRefCitation>
[printed]. There is no precise locality information from the original description or specimen labels, but according to the ac- cession book at 
<collectionCode id="ED42AE16FFB9FFB3FEE8BC40FE4EFD81" box="[336,422,586,612]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="2" pageNumber="536">HNHM</collectionCode>
the type specimen was collected in “Praesidio” (= Presidio) in 
<collectingRegion id="4997F831FFB9FFB3FBCEBC43FAE1FD81" box="[1142,1289,585,612]" country="Mexico" name="Sinaloa" pageId="2" pageNumber="536">Sinaloa state</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3447643FFB9FFB3FAAEBC43FA84FD86" box="[1302,1388,585,611]" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="536">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and purchased from the British naturalist Alphonse Forrer in 1883. The species was correctly interpreted by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFB9FFB3FA87BC67FF33FD4E" author="Snelling, R. R." pageId="2" pageNumber="536" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref6848" refString="Snelling, R. R. (1966) The taxonomy and nomenclature of some North American bees of the genus Centris with description of new species (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae). Contributions in Science, Los Angeles County Museum of Natural History, 112, 1 - 33." type="journal article" year="1966">Snelling (1966</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFB9FFB3FF5FBC9BFEC8FD4E" author="Snelling, R. R." box="[231,288,657,683]" pageId="2" pageNumber="536" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref6899" refString="Snelling, R. R. (1984) Studies on the taxonomy and distribution of American Centridini bees (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae). Contributions in Science, Los Angeles County Museum of Natural History, 347, 1 - 69." type="journal article" year="1984">1984</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFB9FFB3FEE6BC98FDD5FD4E" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[350,573,657,684]" pageId="2" pageNumber="536" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref6580" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFB9FFB3FE08BC98FE09FD4E" box="[432,481,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="536">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
